Borussia Dortmund's £6.3million spent on Shinji Kagawa is soon coming back after the Bundesliga club sold more than 5,000 shirts with the former Manchester United player's name on the back.

Kagawa, in his second spell with Dortmund after starring for them between 2010 and 2012, swapped Old Trafford for the Westfalenstadion on the final day of the transfer window.

And German newspaper Bild stated the lucrative deal for their new No 7 saw thousands of shirts fly off the club shop shelves just hours after the announcement. 

