Kagawa was put through his paces on his return to Dortmund and received an especially warm welcome from manager Jurgen Klopp.

The Japan international's four-year contract was a blessing after injuries caused Kagawa's career to stumble under David Moyes in Manchester. 

United originally bought the playmaker for £12m and cut a near 50 per cent loss on their investment.

